  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DCA&apos;s International Strategy 2015-2018 outlines three overall areas of work:

1. Saving lives
2. Building resilient communities
3. Fighting extreme poverty

DCA&apos;s strategic choice of intervention under these areas are:

1. Active citizenship
2. Right to food
3. Sexual and reproductive health rights
4. Humanitarian action
5. Safer communities. 

The updated International Strategy received in September 2016 reconfirms these five areas of work, and specifies concrete programme activities and indicators under each element. It further specifies that operations will take place in the following countries: Zimbabwe, Kenya, Nepal, Cambodia, Uganda, Burundi/Tanzania, the Sahel, Syria (Turkey/Iraq/Jordan), and Congo/CAR.</narrative>
  </description>
